Package ohos.data.orm

Class DowngradeComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.data.orm.DowngradeComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<OrmMigration>

    public class DowngradeComparator
extends Object
implements Comparator<OrmMigration>
    Represents the comparator for a database downgrade.

    The comparator sorts OrmMigration objects in a descending order of the version number so that the database can be downgraded in the given order. The comparator automatically takes effect during a database downgrade.

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare​(OrmMigration o1,
                   OrmMigration o2)
        Compares the downgrade sequence of two OrmMigration objects.

        The OrmMigration object with a later start version will be downgraded before the other. If the two OrmMigration objects have the same start version, the object with a later end version will be downgraded before the other.

        Specified by:
        compare in interface Comparator<OrmMigration>
        Parameters:
        o1 - Indicates the first OrmMigration object.
        o2 - Indicates the second OrmMigration object.
        Returns:
        Returns -1 if the first object will be downgraded before the second object; returns 0 if the two objects will be downgraded at the same time; returns 1 if the second object will be downgraded before the first object.
        Since:
        1
